IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Detailed Crash Investigation Report (For review by the MSP Crash Team) Section I. - Introduction: On 3/5/2023, at 1417 hours, Troopers from the MSP La Plata Barrack responded to the area of MD Route 6 west of Academy Place, Indian Head, Charles County, Maryland to investigate a motor vehicle collision. Upon Troopers arrival they learned that the crash involved the below listed vehicle and people. The barrack requested a collision reconstructionist. I was notified at 1449 hours and arrived at the scene at 1546 hours. A preliminary investigation revealed that the Ford was driving eastbound on MD Route 6 west of Academy Place. The motorcycle was driving westbound on MD Route 6 west of Academy place. The Ford crossed over the double yellow center line and struck the Motorcycle head-on. The Ford ran off road on the right shoulder of westbound MD Route 6 and came to final rest partially off the roadway. The motorcycle came to final rest, over-turned, beneath the Ford on the right shoulder of westbound MD Route 6. The operator of the motorcycle was pronounced deceased on scene. The driver of the Ford was transported by ground to University of Maryland Charles Regional Hospital with suspected minor injuries. The scene was photographed and measurements were obtained. The roadway closure was maintained by SHA/CHART. Vehicle #1 2002 Ford F-150 MD 2CM7127 OwnerMichael John Phelps (W/M DOB 12/2/1985) of Nanjemoy, MD. Driver- Jeffrey Robert Grasso (W/M DOB 5/12/1985) of Newburg, MD. Vehicle #2 2014 Harley Davidson motorcycle TN K65086 Owner/Operator Alan Michael Reinburg (W/M DOB 4/1/1989) of Grimsley, TN. Witness- Amy Lynn Zagrodnichek (W/F DOB 9/6/1979) of Nanjemoy, MD. Section II. - Scene Description: (The following descriptions are based on the area where the collision occurred.) Primary Roadway: MD Route 6, in the area of the crash was a two-way highway consisting of two travel lanes, traveling in an east/west direction. The roadway consisted of paved asphalt and was dry at the time of the collision. The roadway did not have any defects and was in good condition. The right shoulder was marked by a solid white line, while the yellow center line consisted of a double solid yellow line. The roadway in the area of the collision was on a curve to the right driving in an eastbound direction. The speed limit in the area of the collision was 50 MPH. Environmental Conditions: The weather conditions at the time of the collision was clear with a surface temperature of approximately 83 degrees Fahrenheit. Section III. - Scene Evidence: I arrived at the scene on 3/5/2023, at approximately 1546 hours. I started my scene investigation to the east of the crash scene. I observed no evidence of pre-impact braking from either the Ford or the motorcycle. The Ford and motorcycle came to final rest on the right shoulder of eastbound MD Route 6. I observed a scrape mark indicating the point of impact in the travel portion of the westbound lane of MD Route 6. I documented the scene and roadway evidence with digital photographs. Additional photographs were taken by Sgt Zimmerman using a sUAV. Section IV. - Vehicle(s) Involved: Vehicle #1 2002 Ford F-150 MD 2CM7127 OwnerMichael John Phelps (W/M DOB 12/2/1985) of Nanjemoy, MD. Driver- Jeffrey Robert Grasso (W/M DOB 5/12/1985) of Newburg, MD. At the scene of the crash the Ford was at final rest on right shoulder of eastbound MD Route 6. I observed heavy front end damage consistent with the Ford striking a motorcycle head-on. The Ford had ran over the motorcycle which was beneath the truck behind the front axle. Vehicle #2 2014 Harley Davidson motorcycle TN K65086 Owner/Operator Alan Michael Reinburg (W/M DOB 4/1/1989) of Grimsley, TN. At the scene of the crash the Ford was at final rest on right shoulder of eastbound MD Route 6. The motorcycle was beneath the truck behind the front axle. The damage to the motorcycle was consistent with a head-on collision with the Ford. Section V. - Person(s) Involved: Person #1: Driver of vehicle #1. Jeffrey Robert Grasso (W/M DOB 5/12/1985) of Newburg, MD. Grasso sustained non-life threatening injuries in the crash. Grasso initially agreed to submit to Standardized Field Sobriety Tests but only completed a portion before requesting to be evaluated by EMS. Obvious signs of impairment were not observed. Grassos cellular phone, Samsung model SM-S134 DL (GP) IMEI # 351347077138816, was seized at the scene of the crash for further investigation that Grasso may have been distracted using the phone at the time of the crash. A search warrant has been authored and supplemental report will be completed following analysis of the phone by the MSP Forensic Science Lab. Person #2: Operator of vehicle #2. Alan Michael Reinburg (W/M DOB 4/1/1989) of Grimsley, TN. Reinburg was trapped beneath the Ford at final rest. After being freed from beneath the Ford by Fire/EMS personnel, Reinburg was pronounced deceased at the scene by Charles County EMS. Witness - Amy Lynn Zagrodnichek (W/F DOB 9/6/1979) of Nanjemoy, MD. Zagrodnichek provided a handwritten statement advising the motorcycle was driving westbound on MD Route 6 ahead of her prior to the crash. Zagrodnichek advised she observed the Ford driving eastbound, cross over the center line and strike the motorcycle head-on. Zagrodnichek advised she was able to swerve to the left on the eastbound shoulder of MD Route 6 and avoid striking either vehicle. Zagrodnichek advised her approximate speed at the time of the crash was 55 MPH and the motorcycle was approximately the same speed as her vehicle. Section VI. - Follow-up Investigation: A supplemental report will be completed upon receipt of the OCME autopsy report, and analysis of Grassos cellular phone and medical records. Grassos cell phone was submitted to MSP computer crimes for analysis on 6/27/2023. Section VII. - Analysis of Electronic Control Modules: See supplement completed by Sgt Zimmerman. Section VIII. - Speed Analysis: Due to the lack of available evidence a speed analysis was not conducted beyond analysis of the Fords Electronic Control Module. Section IX. - Crash Dynamics: Investigation revealed that the Ford was driving eastbound on MD Route 6 west of Academy Place. The motorcycle was driving westbound on MD Route 6 west of Academy place. The Ford crossed over the double yellow center line and struck the motorcycle head-on. The Ford ran off road on the right shoulder of westbound MD Route 6 and came to final rest partially off the roadway. The motorcycle came to final rest, over-turned, beneath the Ford on the right shoulder of westbound MD Route 6. The operator of the motorcycle was pronounced deceased on scene. The driver of the Ford was transported by ground to University of Maryland County Regional Hospital with suspected minor injuries. Section X. - Attachments that were included in for this report: The following items were attached to this report: -Automated Crash Report (ACRS) MSP75870012 -One (1) handwritten statement provided by Amy Lynn Zagrodnichek (W/F DOB 9/6/1979). -Maryland State Police Death Investigation Report (Form 89b) -Thirty four (34) digital photographs were taken and uploaded to into the VeriPic Digital Evidence System. Conclusion: This case is open pending results of analysis of Grassos cellular phone, medical records and review by the Charles County States Attorneys Office. Authored By: TFC R. Detailed Crash Investigation Supplement (For review by the MSP Crash Team) Section I. - Introduction: On 3/5/2023, at 1417 hours, Troopers from the MSP La Plata Barrack responded to the area of MD Route 6 west of Academy Place, Indian Head, Charles County, Maryland to investigate a motor vehicle collision. Upon Troopers arrival they learned that the crash involved the below listed vehicle and people. The barrack requested a collision reconstructionist. I was notified at 1449 hours and arrived at the scene at 1546 hours. Section II. - Follow-up Investigation: On 8/9/2023, I received medical records for Jeffrey Robert Grasso (W/M DOB 5/12/1985). The records reveal Grasso was treated for injuries sustained in the crash. Grasso sustained a left mid clavicle fracture with approximately one shaft width displacement. Analysis of Grassos blood was not conducted. Grasso reported to the emergency department staff he was currently taking Adderall and Suboxone. The report is not specific enough to determine whether Grasso may have been under the influence of a controlled dangerous substance at the time of the crash. On 8/25/2023, I received a forensic analysis of Grassos cellular telephone conducted by TFC T. Phillips, a digital forensics examiner with the MSP Criminal Enforcement Division. Analysis of the cellular phone revealed the following: -The device events shows the Display On/Off event as on a total of 8 times between 1338 hours and 1409 hours. -The call log shows outgoing calls being placed at 1410 hours and 1415 hours. -The Instant Message section of the report shows the following texts sent from Grassos phone: -At 1406 hours Well thats nasty just doing stuff around his house again this needs big things of firewood and raking until I got hard ass work either my third fourth or fifth day awake so I keep falling asleep like standing up sent to 240-923-8883. -At 1412 hours Oh my God I just got into an accident I swerved in the oncoming Lane and ran a motorcycle guy over hes dead in the middle of the road I broke my collarbone sent to 240-923-8883. -At 1515 hours I am going to overdose as soon as I get home if I even get home I think I might go to jail Section III. - Attachments that were included in for this report: The following items were attached to this report: -Medical records from University of Maryland Charles Region Medical Center for patient Jeffrey Robert Grasso (W/M DOB 5/12/1985). -Data files recovered from Grassos cellular telephone. Conclusion: Investigation revealed that the Ford was driving eastbound on MD Route 6 west of Academy Place. The motorcycle was driving westbound on MD Route 6 west of Academy place. The Ford crossed over the double yellow center line and struck the Motorcycle head-on. The Ford ran off road on the right shoulder of westbound MD Route 6 and came to final rest partially off the roadway. The motorcycle came to final rest, over-turned, beneath the Ford on the right shoulder of westbound MD Route 6. The operator of the motorcycle, Alan Michael Reinburg (W/M DOB 4/1/1989), was pronounced deceased on scene. The driver of the Ford, Jeffrey Robert Grasso (W/M DOB 5/12/1985), was transported by ground to University of Maryland Charles Regional Hospital with suspected minor injuries. Analysis of Grassos cellular telephone indicate that Grasso may have been using his handheld electronic device prior to and/or at the time of the crash. I made contact with the Charles County control center who advised the 9-1-1 call was placed at 1409 hours placing the exact time of the crash in the approximate timeframe Grasso may have been sending a text message or the display of his cell phone being activated. Grasso additionally sent a test message following the crash stating Oh my God I just got into an accident I swerved in the oncoming Lane and ran a motorcycle guy over hes dead in the middle of the road I broke my collarbone. This case is open pending review by the Charles County States Attorneys Office. Authored By: TFC R. Detailed Crash Investigation Supplement (For review by the MSPCrash Team) Section I. - Narrative On Wednesday, April 05, 2023, at approximately 1417 hours, I responded to Maryland Route 6 at Academy Place, Indian Head, Charles County, Maryland for a fatal motor vehicle collision to assist TFC R. Backus. TFC R. Backus, Regional Collision Reconstructionist responded to the scene to assume the investigation. I forensically mapped the scene utilizing the sUAV (Crash 8). A Notice to Airmen (NOTAM) was established in Class G airspace. On Friday, April 21, 2023, a search and seizure warrant for the Ford F-150 was presented to the Honorable Judge D. Carrington Martin, Circuit Court Judge for Charles County, Maryland. Judge Carrington Martin reviewed the search and seizure warrant and signed the warrant. On Friday, April 21, 2023, I executed the search and seizure warrant for the Ford F-150 at the Maryland State Police La Plata Barrack. I obtained an electronic copy of the Airbag Control Module via the Data Link Connector (DLC). A copy of the warrant and return was placed inside the Ford F-150. 1. Analysis of the Fords EDR Data: a. Software recovered one event stored on the module. b. A review of the Data Limitations section did not reveal any known issues with the data. c. Deployed: i. Pre-Crash Data: 1. The Ford experienced a maximum delta-V of -15.82 MPH at 42 milliseconds during the recording. This delta-V would have been under-reported as the Ford overrode the motorcycle. Please refer to the Crash Data Retrieval System (CDR) report for further which is attached to this supplemental report. Section II. - Attachments that were included in this report: The following items were attached to this report: 1. Scale Diagram 2. Search Warrant and Return 3. ACM/CDR Report 4. Notice to Airmen (NOTAM) The following items have been archived in the Crash Team Files: font-size:10pt">1. CDR File Data font-size:10pt">2. Diagram files font-size:10pt">3. Pix4D files font-size:11pt"> 4. Flight Records Conclusion: This concludes my involvement in this investigation. Author: Sergeant Justin Zimmerman #3901 Maryland State Police Crash Team La Plata Office 9500 Mitchell Road La Plata, Maryland 20646 301-392-1231 Justin.zimmerman@maryland.gov
